Nom Anglais: Freycinet Peninsula Historical Note: It had been sighted by Tasman in 1643, and named 'Van der Lyn', after one of the councillors of the Dutch East India Government (Moore-Robinson). Tas Field Naturalists Notes evidently state that Tasman originally applied the name 'Vanderlin Islands'.
Maurouard Gulch (also Maurouard beach, in St Helen town)
Cape Naturaliste  (Early alternative name was Chapman Point)
